    "body": "If the user supplied both `maxFeePerGas` and `maxPriorityFeePerGas`, replacements should be allowed when only `maxPriorityFeePerGas` is bumped (assuming effective gas has increased as appropriate).  Requiring both to be bumped prevents use of the feecap as an arbitrarily high set-and-forget hard limit, harming the user experience.  I see how the bumping feecap could allow a spam attack, but not the tip.",
